It's time for it's own forum. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uredspinebladeslinge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Redspine Bladeslinge</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 453<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/10/01 12:28:11 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/yellowspine/Redspine_1.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoG forum</span><hr size=1> Once again....agree. <p><b>Redspine Bladeslinger - 56th Myrmidon</b><br>
Jestur - 48th Cleric <br>
Whitefange - 16th Shaman<br>
Member of Lost Adventurers<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unillon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nillon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>GD RPers</span><br>  Posts: 1450<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/10/01 5:12:51 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/soj/nillon.jpg height=306 width=162></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoG forum</span><hr size=1> The problem is it'd need it's own standards, and i'm worried that opening a forum would encourage people who normally wouldn't want to go to PoG to sign up to preserve their &quot;rights&quot;. I don't really have a problem with a forum in general there just needs to be a topic discussion growth's rules first. <p>nillon<br>
60 warlord<br>
<a href ="http://sr.amiga.tm">Silent Redemption</a><br>
Champion of Brell <br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usadara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sadara</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 400<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/11/01 3:18:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoG forum</span><hr size=1> Let's get the forum up and use the same rules that the other planes use.  We can discuss what they should be as we go along.  But a forum is needed now.  Raid Intentions is cluddered with PoG raids.<br>
<br>
 <p><center><a href="http://www.krunch.net/spiritslammer/index4.htm">
<img border="0" src="http://home.kscable.com/sadara/images/sadararezstick.jpg" width="562" height="165"><br>
</a><font color="#FFFFFF"><font face="Arial"><br><font size="2"><b><i>"Sparkles!!  I see Sparkles!!"</i><br></b>-- Cleric of the 53rd Season --<br>

</font><font size="3">

-- <a href="http://home.kscable.com/sadara/photoalbum.htm"> <font color="#FFFFFF">Spiritslammer Family Album</font></a>
--</font><font size="2"><br></font></font>
</center>
</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaphdia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saphdia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 1262<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/11/01 3:42:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoG forum</span><hr size=1> After exploring POG, I have to agree with Nillon here.  I think it having the same claims as the other planes might not be the right way to go as it looks like POG can handle a few groups raiding it.  If it goes with the same guidelines, I'm afraid that one group will lay claim to it when it really can support 2.  Might as well get the ball rolling in the right way.  Maybe this can be the thread?  or someone can start another one?<br>
<br>
Saph <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 248<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/11/01 11:14:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoG forum</span><hr size=1> Why not simply have a PoG Forum but its only for &quot;Intentions&quot; as it is now.  Nothing changes other than all the raids are listed in the same spot and not cluttering up the &quot;Others&quot; forum.  No rules are needed.  Its an Intentions plane only.  Lets not make rules until we know more about what needs to be set up.  I think that the crowd going to PoG (mostly 53+) can work together well enough for now on an intentions basis. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugrombdabasher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gromb Da Basher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/12/01 3:41:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoG forum</span><hr size=1> Problem here is that you can have a group of 24 in one area, and another group of the same amount in a different spot all hunting different mobs and never see each other..<br>
That Zone will take alot of people to actually clear and get to some of the final mobs as hard as it is to get all the people you need and get them there early enough to get thru it all.<br>
 <p>Gromb DaBasher
54th lvl warrior
"Elysian"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usadara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sadara</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 404<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/12/01 8:40:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoG forum</span><hr size=1> I saw in another forum that Nillon mentioned going North or South, I'm assuming from the portal.  Why not setup the forum so that two raids can be hosted per day.  Sign up would require you to state if you are heading north of the portal or south of the portal.  I would think that any more than 2 raiding parties would lag to zone out too much.<br>
<br>
 <p><center><a href="http://www.krunch.net/spiritslammer/index4.htm">
<img border="0" src="http://home.kscable.com/sadara/images/sadararezstick.jpg" width="562" height="165"><br>
</a><font color="#FFFFFF"><font face="Arial"><br><font size="2"><b><i>"Sparkles!!  I see Sparkles!!"</i><br></b>-- Cleric of the 53rd Season --<br>

</font><font size="3">

-- <a href="http://home.kscable.com/sadara/photoalbum.htm"> <font color="#FFFFFF">Spiritslammer Family Album</font></a>
--</font><font size="2"><br></font></font>
</center>
</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uatwork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AtWork</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 216<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/12/01 11:02:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoG forum</span><hr size=1> I have a question about PoG itself.<br>
<br>
I've only raided it once, but I think that the armors drops are segregated in the plain.  When I went, once you moved past a point, it seemed that some drops stopped for certain classes.<br>
<br>
Is this true?  If it is, would it cause arguments about which class goes in what direction?<br>
<br>
The questions are born of my ignorance of the zone and my curiosity.  I'm sorry that I've started to have doubts about the nature of some folks.  But after raiding Hate several times and seeing the cries of pull this mob, etc., I have this concern about PoG.<br>
<br>
Tatter D'Malion<br>
Rent-A-Bard <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujuujuu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Juujuu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 376<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/13/01 6:09:16 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/snchicktourney/larges/18.jpg width=140 height=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoG forum</span><hr size=1> Stuff to consider rules for bookings in PoG.<br>
<br>
Depending on what mobs you are killing, it determines the difficulty of the mob, as well as what class, and what body slot the armor is that will drop.<br>
<br>
The zone respawns in 30 hours.  This means that if someone starts a raid, say, at noon on one day, the repops won't start happening the next day until about 6pm, and the next raid the next day would have to start at midnight, and the next one at 6am the next day.<br>
<br>
The zone is large enough that in order to clear it in one day, you'd need about 30 people working for well over 15 or 20 hours straight with frantic pulling going on.  People don't do this for raids.  As such, the Plane is actually big enough to support 2 separate raids, one going north to the waterfall, and one going south across the lake.  Pulling everything on the near side of the river is comparable to clearing hate or the armor droppers in fear.<br>
<br>
Posting bookings/intentions to raid the PoG need coordination with other people on what time breakins are done, because of the 30 hour spawn time.  If someone is doing a raid the day/night before, it's quite possible to post an intention to try and do some of the treants, assuming that you begin your raid soon after the previous raid ends.  Also, if you see someone posting a raid, and you want to go the day before, you shouldn't post your raid to start at a time that will significantly interupte the time that the next one starts.  Soemthing else to consider is if someone is intending to pull treants, they will need the full 30 hours to do so if they take the same raid group on 2 days, or need to take many more people than the standard raid group).  Raids shouldn't be allowed within 30 hours of a previous raid if the previous raid is intending to do treants.<br>
<br>
Just stuff to consider.<br>
Talk amongst yourself. <p>=============================
<br>Juujuu Bigmojo
